## Input System

### SceneInputHandler (`src/engine/SceneInputHandler.hpp/.cpp`)

**Action Mappings**:

```cpp
"move_left"    → KEY_A
"move_right"   → KEY_D
"move_up"      → KEY_W
"move_down"    → KEY_S
"jump"         → KEY_SPACE
"interact"     → KEY_E
"pause"        → KEY_P
"accept"       → KEY_ENTER
"cancel"       → KEY_ESCAPE
```

**Input States**:
- Pressed (P) - Single frame on key down
- Held (H) - Every frame while key is down
- Released (R) - Single frame on key up

### Input in Scenes

```cpp
// Check action state
if (ih->isActionPressed("jump")) {
    // Jump logic
}

// Get raw key state
if (ih->isKeyHeld(KEY_LEFT_SHIFT)) {
    // Sprint logic
}

// Get mouse position
Vector2 mouseWorld = ih->getMouseWorldPosition();
```

---

## Asset System

### AssetPack (`src/engine/AssetPack.hpp/.cpp`)

**Format**: `assets.rres` - Packed resource file

**Loading Patterns**:

```cpp
// Single texture
Texture2D tex = AssetPack::loadTexture("gotchis/001/idle_00.png");

// Multiple frames (numbered sequence)
std::vector<Texture2D> frames = AssetPack::loadFrames("gotchis/001", "idle");

// Unload
AssetPack::unloadFrames(frames);
```

**Asset Keys** (relative to assets.rres root):
- `"gotchis/001/idle_00.png"`
- `"gotchis/001/walk_00.png"`
- `"ui/buttons/menu_button.png"`

---

## Key Bindings (Keyboard)

| Key | Scene | Function |
|-----|-------|----------|
| 1 | Any | Switch to GameScene |
| 2 | Any | Switch to BossScene |
| 3 | Any | Switch to InputTestScene |
| 4 | Any | Switch to SpriteTestScene |
| 5 | Any | Switch to HexViewScene |
| 7 | Any | Switch to SceneSelectScene |
| 8 | Any | Switch to GotchiScene |
| 0 | Game/Boss | Toggle pause menu |
| SPACE | Game/Boss | Skip dialog or advance |
| H | Game/Boss | Replay dialog from start |
| E | Narrative scenes | Trigger next event |
| R | InputTest | Toggle key rebinding mode |
| ESC | All | Exit game |

---

## Summary

The Hexagotchi rendering system provides:

1. **Scene-based architecture** - 12 distinct scenes with custom rendering
2. **Actor system** - Layered rendering with physics and animation
3. **Camera system** - Follow, zoom, shake, and lookahead
4. **Effect system** - Parallax stars and 3D moon with shaders
5. **Transition effects** - Fade and slide transitions between scenes
6. **Dialog system** - Shared dialogue box with typing reveal and options
7. **Input system** - Action mapping with rebinding support
8. **Asset packing** - Single rres file for all resources

The system balances simplicity (base Scene/SceneActor classes) with flexibility (custom draw() methods per scene) to support both gameplay and narrative scenes.
